  "text": "A sample of lignosulphonate (100 g), dissolved in 2 M sodium hydroxide (7 ℓ) was prepared in the same manner as previously described and transferred to the digester described above. A powdered sample of CuSO 4 •5H 2 O (512 g), identified as a suitable catalyst in literature, was added to the solution in a 4:1 molar ratio with lignin (average molar mass of 195 g•mol -1 ) and the mixture was allowed to heat up in a stepwise manner to 170°C [CITATION_1] ). The reaction vessel was vented and the oxygen flushed and bubbled through the solution as described above. The temperature was maintained at 170°C and a pressure of 900 kPa for 2.5 h with continuous rotation.",
